---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="D&D 5E Guide - House Rules">
	<div class="content">
		<h1>House Rules</h1>

		<section class="rule-section">
			<h2>Critical Hits</h2>
			<p>When you score a critical hit, instead of rolling the damage dice twice, maximize the first set of dice and roll the second set normally. This ensures critical hits feel more impactful.</p>
		</section>

		<section class="rule-section">
			<h2>Death Saves</h2>
			<p>Death saving throw results remain hidden from other players unless a character uses their action to check on the dying character with a DC 10 Medicine check.</p>
		</section>

		<section class="rule-section">
			<h2>Inspiration</h2>
			<p>Players can earn inspiration for:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Exceptional roleplay</li>
				<li>Creative problem-solving</li>
				<li>Advancing personal character arcs</li>
				<li>Taking notes and maintaining session summaries</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="rule-section">
			<h2>Short Rests</h2>
			<p>Short rests take 30 minutes instead of 1 hour to encourage their use and maintain game pacing.</p>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.content {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.rule-section {
		background: var(--card-bg);
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
		border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
	}

	h2 {
		color: var(--primary);
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	ul {
		margin-left: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	li {
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}
</style>